title: Independent Candidate Muhammad Tahir wins PP-284 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Independent Candidate, Muhammad Tahir has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-284, Taunsa-I by securing 52,574 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Sardar Mir Badshah Khan Qaisrani of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 48,633 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 56.34%.
